<tr bgcolor="CCCCCC">
<td><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000"><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Session=" OnMouseOver="window.status='Back to EverQuest.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><b>Home</a> / <a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowCategory&Category=default&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" OnMouseOver="window.status='View this (Character Classes) category.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><b>Character Classes</b></a> / <a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowBoard&Board=rogue&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" OnMouseOver="window.status='Back to Rogues board.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''">Rogues</b></a></font></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/Message.gif" border="0"></td><td width="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000"> <b>Rogue Race Analysis</b> <img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/New.gif" border="0"></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000">Pros and Cons of Each Rogue Race</font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><p><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER" bgcolor="000000">
<tr>
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" align="CENTER">
<tr bgcolor="999999">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/SmallNew.gif" border="0" alt="New Message"></td><td width="50%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Rogue Race Analysis (modified 0 times)</b> </font></td><td width="50%" align="RIGHT"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>WebSlinger</b></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=webslinger&Board=rogue&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View WebSlinger (webslinger) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Since it seems that every board on this site is flooded in "Which race makes the best soandso?" messages in which people childishly bicker, most of whom are l33t d00ds who religiously uphold the most cliched race, I think it would be a good idea to post one big-ass thread with a full analysis of the races so that instead of someone posting a new "best race" thread every single week, they can just refer to this one.  To start off, I've decided to analyze the class that I know best:  the Rogue.  What will follow in this post is an analysis of each Rogue race, with pros and cons, and will actually be something of a preview of an article I will write someday when I get bored enough.  The article will list every race/class combination in order of popularity (which I found by going "/ all halfling rogue count", "/ all wood rogue count", etc.) with their stats and my personal editorial analysis of the combination.  The editorial will be pretty much in the same style as what you are about to see.<p>

I invite everyone who reads this post (that's right, both of you) to add your feelings.  For the sake of presenting an interesting thread, please be prepared to list both the pros AND cons of whichever race(s) you choose to comment on.  Now without further ado:<p>

WebSlinger's Half-Assed Analysis of the Rogue Races<p>

Average Stats<br>
STR:  74.125 (maximum and average damage with hits, how much you can carry; not one of the Rogue's "primary attributes," but still extremely important)<br>
AGI:  95.25 (how much AC you get, factors into success rate of evade, how often you dodge, how quickly you learn defensive skills)<br>
DEX:  91.25 (how often you hit or miss, how quickly you learn offensive skills and Rogue-specific skills, how often weapon spell procs go off)<p>

(Races listed in alphabetical order)<p>

Barbarian<br>
STR:  103;  STA:  95;  AGI:   92;  DEX:   80;  WIS:  70;  INT:  60;  CHA:  55<br>
ARMOR:  Medium and large (ideally medium)<br>
Highest strength of any Rogue race, and since the Rogue plays in a group as the best damage-dealer of the melee classes, strength is important.  High stamina helps make up for the Rogue's second biggest hindrance, low HP (the first being that you have to be behind an enemy to do any real damage).  Agility is almost average (but high enough, in my opinion anyway).  Dexterity, however, leaves something to be desired.  Faction isn't very good with Rogues of other races, but that's why Rogues have sneak.  Armor might be harder to find for this race, since medium and large aren't as easy to find as small, but having the choice of two sizes gives you a bit more selection.  Barbarians have access to some large-race-only throwing weapons, which could be of an obvious benefit should you decide to exploit the Rogue's innate ability to get critical hits with throwing.  I would put twenty-five points into dexterity and five into strength.<p>

Dark Elf<br>
STR:   60;  STA:  65;  AGI:  100;  DEX:   85;  WIS:  83;  INT:  99;  CHA:  60<br>
ARMOR:  Small and medium (ideally small)<br>
Strength is god-awful, but agility is excellent, and dexterity isn't half bad.  The Teir'Dal Rogue is right up there with the Feir'Dal as one of the easiest Rogue races to find armor for.  On PvP-Teams servers, Dark Elves are the only evil race that can choose the Rogue class.  I would put everything you've got into strength.<p>

Dwarf<br>
STR:   90;  STA:  90;  AGI:   80;  DEX:  100;  WIS:  83;  INT:  60;  CHA:  45<br>
ARMOR:  Small<br>
The only Rogue race with strength that even comes close to the Barbarians in the raw strength department.  Like the Barbarians, Dwarves have high stamina which will partially make up for the Rogue's low HP.  Agility is pretty lacking, but dexterity is tied with Halflings for the highest of any Rogue race.  My recommendation is to put ten or fifteen points into agility, and the rest into strength.<p>

Gnome<br>
STR:   60;  STA:  70;  AGI:   95;  DEX:   95;  WIS:  67;  INT:  98;  CHA:  60<br>
ARMOR:  Small<br>
I must say I have a real soft spot in my heart for Gnomes, especially the little Gnome ninjas.  Strength is right down there with the Dark Elves, but agility and dexterity both rock.  Put everything you have into strength, and you'll be set.<p>

Half Elf<br>
STR:   70;  STA:  70;  AGI:  100;  DEX:   95;  WIS:  60;  INT:  75;  CHA:  75<br>
ARMOR:  Medium<br>
Strength is below average, agility is excellent, and dexterity is above average.  Armor is tied with Humans for the hardest to find of any Rogue race.  Half Elves are cool because your religion choice can make you either good or evil.  Put everything you've got into strength.<p>

Halfling<br>
STR:   70;  STA:  75;  AGI:  105;  DEX:  100;  WIS:  80;  INT:  67;  CHA:  50<br>
ARMOR:  Small<br>
Strength is below average, but agility and dexterity are tied with that of Wood Elves and Dwarves, respectively, for the highest of any race, Rogue or otherwise.  Halflings get sneak and hide as racial abilities, which will come in handy until level ten, when you skill will surpass the racial ability cap of fifty.  Halflings also level the fastest of any race.  Put it all into strength.<p>

Human<br>
STR:   75;  STA:  75;  AGI:   85;  DEX:   85;  WIS:  75;  INT:  75;  CHA:  75<br>
ARMOR:  Medium<br>
Strength is average, while agility and dexterity are slightly below average.  Armor can be a problem, since you're limited to medium.  My favorite thing about this race is that they have more deity selections than any other species, so you have many roleplaying possibilities if you choose the path of the Human Rogue.  I would recommend allocating fifteen of your starting points into strength, five into agility, and ten into dexterity.  It would also work to put ten into strength and ten into agility.<p>

Wood Elf<br>
STR:   65;  STA:  65;  AGI:  105;  DEX:   90;  WIS:  80;  INT:  75;  CHA:  75<br>
ARMOR:  Small and medium (ideally small)<br>
Strength is almost as low as that of Dark Elves and Gnomes, and dexterity is about average, but agility is tied with Halflings for the highest in the game.  The Feir'Dal are easy to find armor for, and get forage as a racial ability.  I would put all of your starting points into strength.<p>

---<p>

Remember, stats aren't everything.  It's also very important to choose a race based on how you want to roleplay (although this is usually very versatile).  Personal preference varies, so no one can say that there is a "best" Rogue race.  Personally, my favorites are Halflings, Dwarves, and Barbarians, the first of which is actually the race of my Rogue.  But I'm no expert on EQ (or much else for that matter), so don't just listen to what I have to say.  Remember that every race has something to offer that no other race can equal.<p>

Any feedback is welcomed.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
